Futaba: I really liked the still-life drawing you made today, Ena.
Ena: Huh? Really...?
Futaba: Yeah. The glass you drew looked so real, and you did such a good job with that lemon's shadow. It felt really three-dimensional.
Futaba: Plus, Mr. Yukihira didn't seem to have any complaints regarding those things.
Ena: Right.
Ena: (Thank goodness. I feel like I'm starting to get better at doing sketches.)
Ena: (My progress has been slow, but it's good to know that I'm improving. And I just gotta keep trying...)
Yukihira: Lastly, I have an announcement to make.
Ena: An announcement...?
Futaba: What do think he's going to talk about?
Yukihira: As I do each year, I'll be holding a special course on technical mastery for those aiming to get into art school.
Yukihira: I strongly suggest to all prospective applicants to not pass up this opportunity.
Ena: Oh...
